  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 889faa658c7b2c94ea4fff939bf8022e, type: 3}
  m_Name: DialogNPCTutorial
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  Name: Rocco
  Icon: {fileID: -2105629146, guid: d556a7f542c7d03429c5a535ce31a084, type: 3}
  HasInteraction: 0
  interactionType: 3
  Greeting: Marshal (11 Labs)
  Day1Dialog:
  - "I don\u2019t know what brought you to this bombarded fort, son, but you\u2019re
    here now, and we\u2019re glad to have another pair of hands. No one comes to
    St Elmo by accident, not at this time.\n\nListen to me for a moment. We\u2019re
    under siege from both the sea and from Mount Sciberras. The guns out there are
    still finding their aim, so today you\u2019ll have a bit more freedom to move
    around. The walls aren\u2019t breached yet; you can still cross the yard without
    climbing over half the fort. That won\u2019t last. As the days pass, their bombardment
    will grow heavier, and getting anywhere will mean stepping around craters and
    fallen stone.\n\nPress F for more"
  - "If you want proper orders, go and speak with Colonel Mas. You\u2019ll find him
    near the building in the middle of the fort. He\u2019ll assign you your work.
    Just remember this: you only get one task each day. Once you choose where to
    help, that\u2019s all you\u2019ll have time and strength for, so choose carefully.\n\nIn
    each place you\u2019re sent\u2014the armoury, the infirmary, the engineers\u2019
    works\u2014you\u2019ll find the master in charge. Talk to them. You\u2019ll learn
    more than just how to lift or carry.\nThere are others worth talking to as well.
    \n\nPress F for more"
  - "A friend of mine keeps watch up on the cavalier at the back of the fort. And
    at the front, there\u2019s an Italian knight who has a very good understanding
    about the fort and our enemies. If you have the courage, go hear them too.\n\nIf
    you take a hit and go down, we\u2019ll drag you back here and patch you up as
    best we can. You\u2019ll live, but you\u2019ll lose the day. Around here, a lost
    day can cost other people more than it costs you.\n\nI still don\u2019t know
    why you chose to come to St Elmo of all places and at this time, but I\u2019m
    not going to push you about it. Whatever your reason is, hold on to it. In a
    place like this, you\u2019ll need something of your own to follow, not just orders
    shouted over cannon fire."
  Day2FirstTimeDialog:
  - "You\u2019re back on your feet. Good. Most men spend their first night here wondering
    how to sneak back to Birgu, but you stayed. That tells me something.\nThe Grand
    Master doesn\u2019t want this fort abandoned, and I suppose he sees something
    stubborn in all of us. We hold as long as we can \u2014 that\u2019s the job.\nDon\u2019t
    worry yourself with how long that means. Thinking too far ahead is how a man
    loses his nerve. Just focus on today. Help where you can. A single pair of hands
    makes more difference here than you\u2019d expect.\n\nPress F for more"
  - "If you want somewhere to start, try the infirmary. They always need help \u2014
    hear out the stories of the fallen and bandage them up. Some of those men might
    see their homes again because a stranger stood beside them for an hour.\nAs for
    me\u2026 my family is safe in Birgu. I don\u2019t dwell on the rest \u2014 it
    won\u2019t help anyone. You do your part, and we\u2019ll keep this place standing
    a little longer.\nAnd remember: no one here expects you to save the world. Just
    pick something and see it through for the day. That\u2019s enough."
  Day2MetBeforeDialog:
  - "You\u2019re back on your feet. Good. Most men spend their first night here wondering
    how to sneak back to Birgu, but you stayed. That tells me something.\nThe Grand
    Master doesn\u2019t want this fort abandoned, and I suppose he sees something
    stubborn in all of us. We hold as long as we can \u2014 that\u2019s the job.\nDon\u2019t
    worry yourself with how long that means. Thinking too far ahead is how a man
    loses his nerve. Just focus on today. Help where you can. A single pair of hands
    makes more difference here than you\u2019d expect.\n\nPress F for more"
  - "If you want somewhere to start, try the infirmary. They always need help \u2014
    hear out the stories of the fallen and bandage them up. Some of those men might
    see their homes again because a stranger stood beside them for an hour.\n\nAs
    for me\u2026 my family is safe in Birgu. I don\u2019t dwell on the rest \u2014
    it won\u2019t help anyone. You do your part, and we\u2019ll keep this place standing
    a little longer.\n\nAnd remember: no one here expects you to save the world.
    Just pick something and see it through for the day. That\u2019s enough."
  Day3FirstTimeDialog:
  - "I\u2019ve got family in Birgu. I think about them when the guns quiet down,
    and that\u2019s enough for me. They\u2019re safer there than we are here, and
    that\u2019s how it should be.\n\nIf you\u2019re looking for someone of your own,
    keep at it. Don\u2019t let anyone talk you out of hope. Around here, that\u2019s
    the one thing a man can hold without armour or orders.\n\nJust mind yourself
    when you move about \u2014 the fort shifts a little every day. You stay steady,
    keep your purpose close, and you\u2019ll manage fine."
  Day3MetBeforeDialog:
  - "I\u2019ve got family in Birgu. I think about them when the guns quiet down,
    and that\u2019s enough for me. They\u2019re safer there than we are here, and
    that\u2019s how it should be.\n\nIf you\u2019re looking for someone of your own,
    keep at it. Don\u2019t let anyone talk you out of hope. Around here, that\u2019s
    the one thing a man can hold without armour or orders.\n\nJust mind yourself
    when you move about \u2014 the fort shifts a little every day. You stay steady,
    keep your purpose close, and you\u2019ll manage fine."
  Day4FirstTimeDialog:
  - "Easy now, boy. Word is that Turgut Reis has taken charge of their guns. We call
    him Dragut. You\u2019ll hear that name more than you\u2019d like.\n\nHe\u2019s
    not some sea thief chasing prizes \u2014 he knows how to break a position clean.
    You may notice the difference when you walk the yard. The shots are coming from
    all sides now, and they\u2019re landing with purpose.\n\nDon\u2019t panic. It
    just means you move slower and pay attention to the stone under your feet. The
    fort\u2019s still standing, and so are we. You keep your head down, do your day\u2019s
    work, and keep whatever reason brought you here close \u2014 that matters more
    than the noise."
  Day4MetBeforeDialog:
  - "Easy now, boy. Word is that Turgut Reis has taken charge of their guns. We call
    him Dragut. You\u2019ll hear that name more than you\u2019d like.\n\nHe\u2019s
    not some sea thief chasing prizes \u2014 he knows how to break a position clean.
    You may notice the difference when you walk the yard. The shots are coming from
    all sides now, and they\u2019re landing with purpose.\n\nDon\u2019t panic. It
    just means you move slower and pay attention to the stone under your feet. The
    fort\u2019s still standing, and so are we. You keep your head down, do your day\u2019s
    work, and keep whatever reason brought you here close \u2014 that matters more
    than the noise."
  Day5FirstTimeDialog:
  - "Did you sleep at all? I keep waking with the feeling that someone\u2019s going
    to be in the wrong place at the wrong moment today. It\u2019s just a thought,
    but after enough nights under bombardment, a man learns to trust the feeling
    in his gut.\n\nDon\u2019t think about legacies or names. The nobles have their
    scribes. Men like us are lucky if someone remembers we stood on these stones.
    I\u2019ve made peace with that.\n\nPress F for more"
  - "What I can\u2019t shake is the sense that you should stay closer to the walls
    today\u2014closer to people. The dark corners of this fort feel hungrier than
    usual.\n\nMaybe it\u2019s nothing. Maybe it\u2019s just age talking. But keep
    near others, boy. No one should be caught alone right now."
  Day5MetBeforeDialog:
  - "Did you sleep at all? I keep waking with the feeling that someone\u2019s going
    to be in the wrong place at the wrong moment today. It\u2019s just a thought,
    but after enough nights under bombardment, a man learns to trust the feeling
    in his gut.\n\nDon\u2019t think about legacies or names. The nobles have their
    scribes. Men like us are lucky if someone remembers we stood on these stones.
    I\u2019ve made peace with that.\n\nPress F for more"
  - "What I can\u2019t shake is the sense that you should stay closer to the walls
    today\u2014closer to people. The dark corners of this fort feel hungrier than
    usual.\n\nMaybe it\u2019s nothing. Maybe it\u2019s just age talking. But keep
    near others, boy. No one should be caught alone right now."
